FBIS4-9027 "dreeu076__a94045" FBIS-EEU-94-076-A Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 ANNEX Hungary Peto Foresees Stable Government After Elections Peto Foresees Stable Government After Elections AU1804183294 Budapest MTI in English 1643 GMT 18 Apr 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU1804183294 Budapest MTI English BFN [Text] Budapest, 18 Apr (MTI) -- A stable government is assured in the wake of Hungary's parliamentary elections in May, in spite of the fact that certain parties are trying scare tactics on the population with their election remarks, Ivan Peto, the chairman of Hungary's largest opposition party, the Alliance of Free Democrats (AFD), said at a press conference in Zalaegerszeg (W Hungary) on Monday. According to the AFD Chairman, a coalition of parties collectively holding a 60 per cent majority of the votes would guarantee a secure governing position. Peto was of the opinion that votes between the liberal parties and the Socialist Party will decide who will replace the current government.
